data.description: CONTINUING TO SHOW FOR BACK-UP OFFERS: This 6 BDRM, 5 BATH home on a finished basement is nestled in the Morningbrooke neighborhood, a swim and tennis community with almost 1.5 miles of nature trails, bridges, and boardwalks following the gently flowing Suwannee Creek. Highly coveted neighborhood located in Buford, this home is truly special. Step inside from the cozy front porch to a welcoming 2-story foyer separating the formal living room and separate dining room. This very spacious floor plan has beautiful hardwoods covering the entire main floor, complete with a guest bedroom that can also be utilized as an office. The large kitchen w/island and breakfast area has a view to the family room with FP and walk-out to the covered/screened-in deck that overlooks the private wooded backyard; great for relaxing after a hard days work and/or tons of room to host large gatherings. Moving to the upper level, the master suite features a sitting area w/FP, double vanities, jetted tub, and walk-in closet. Three additional guest bedrooms, one with an en suite bathroom, and another full bath complete the upstairs. The finished daylight basement includes a recreation/game room with a stunning wet bar including a sink, microwave, dishwasher, mini-fridge, and ice maker. The terrace level also has an incredible home theater room, a bedroom, full bath, bonus/exercise room, and lots of storage. Excellent highly desirable Lanier High School cluster, close to major shopping, restaurants, and highway access. Don't miss this incredible opportunity to add your personal touches and make this your new home in this amazing location.
